Subject: [PATCH RFC] b43: AC-PHY: flesh out stubs into compilable scaffolding

This is a scaffolding patch on top of Rafał Miłecki's January 2015 AC-PHY
stub. The 2015 stub registered b43_phyops_ac with only 8 members; the
b43 core unconditionally dereferences several ops that were left NULL
(notably ->init and ->software_rfkill, called by b43_phy_init() in
phy_common.c, which is consistent with the "BUG: NULL pointer
dereference at 0000000000000000" reported by users).

This patch:

  * Adds every PHY operation that phy_common.h documents as
    "Must not be NULL" (prepare_structs, init, phy_read, phy_write,
    software_rfkill, switch_analog, switch_channel). Bodies are skeletons
    modelled on b43/phy_ht.c (the closest BCMA-only sibling).
  * Splits the file into the same sections as phy_ht.c (Radio, RF,
    Various PHY ops, Channel switching, Basic PHY ops, R/W, PHY ops
    struct), so that future work has the same structure as for the
    HT-PHY.
  * Introduces tables_phy_ac.{c,h} and radio_2069.{c,h} as placeholders.
  * Extends struct b43_phy_ac with the per-device state that the init
    flow needs (saved RF ctrl, idle TSSI, bb_mult, tx_pwr_idx, tx_pwr_ctl).
  * Adds the register #defines used by the skeleton (RF_CTL1, RF_SEQ_*,
    AFE_C{1,2,3}{,_OVER}, EXTG/OFDM, TXPCTL_*, IQLOCAL_CMDGCTL, SAMP_*,
    TEST). Their numeric offsets are TODOs: see comments.

It is NOT meant to make the device work. Kconfig stays BROKEN. The
device still cannot Tx/Rx because:

  * the PHY init tables are placeholders (see tables_phy_ac.c),
  * the 2069 radio init/channel sequences are placeholders
    (see radio_2069.c),
  * the channel-table values are not populated,
  * no open-source ucode42 firmware exists.

The goal is to have a structure where each missing piece is a function
with a TODO that says exactly where to look:
  - b43/phy_ht.c              for b43-side ops layout (BCMA, MIMO),
  - brcmsmac/phy/phy_n.c      for init flow (wlc_phy_init_nphy),
  - bcm-v4.sipsolutions.net   for register documentation,
  - the wl proprietary blob   if/where licence allows extraction.

Not-Signed-off-by: nobody (this is RFC scaffolding, do not apply)
